cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised video object segmentation, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new technique to establish dense correspondences between pixel embeddings, which involves learning pairwise dependencies at arbitrarily long distances. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
